HEADWORD: Preoccupation
<hw>Pre*oc`cu*pa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praeoccupatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pr⟦eacute⟧occupation</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of preoccupying, or taking possession of
beforehand; the state of being preoccupied; prepossession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anticipation of objections.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preoccupy</ent>⟦br⟧
